Method Detail

setActiveClassName

public void setActiveClassName(java.lang.String acName)
Sets the name of the active class whose state is stored in this map. In order to support nested passivate and activate operations, the acName parameter is a list of colon separated class names.

Parameters:
acName - the name of the active class.

getActiveClassName

public java.lang.String getActiveClassName()
Returns the name of the active class whose state is stored in this map. In order to support nested passivate and activate operations, the returned value is a list of colon separated class names.

Returns:
the class name of the active class.
